parameters:
\SE[0]Oh my! Tita-chan! \SE[0]I'm relieved. You're safe
too!

\SE[0]Tita, huh. \SE[1]Luna helped me before, so...
\SE[2]That's why...

\SE[0]What is this...? \SE[51]Could it be... love at first
sight for Luna? \SE[100]I think I might have...
\SE[60]fallen for her...?

\SE[2]Laura, you're being childish. \SE[57]Just let me talk
to her for a bit...

\SE[19]Don't stop me, Vita...! \SE[33]My instincts are...
whispering to me that she's dangerous...!!

\SE[45]Calm down already? \SE[16]Come on... Be more...
mature...!

\SE[116]Ouch...!!! My strength...!! \SE[34]I'm going to
break! I'm going to break...!!

\SE[16]Today, I went to the flower field with my mother!
\SE[0]I made a flower ring that I thought would suit Lady
Lunaroa, but...
\SE[45]Oh my... I'm happy. \SE[45]I'll gladly accept it.

\SE[16]Thank you very much! \!\SE[42]Um, then, let me take
your hand... Excuse me... \!\SE[51]Wow... Your fingers are
so slender... They're very beautiful.
\SE[2]Oh? \.Is it a little big for my pinky finger?

\SE[44]U-Um, then the ring finger... I wonder...? \SE[46]May
I... put it on... for you...? *panting*

\SE[0]Ah, it fits perfectly. \SE[0]Thank you for the
lovely present.

\SE[6]Oh... I'm so happy. \SE[52]Lady Lunaroa... You're so
beautiful.

I've lost a lot of things... but... it's not just sad
things, right? There were also wonderful things... I think
so too.

I... I want to become stronger. Truly... to the point where
I can protect everyone...

Hmm... I have some free time until it's time to go out.
Maybe I should tease Ryan a bit...

It seems like she wants to say something, but she can't find
her voice...

Lunaroa... Since then, you haven't been able to speak. I
can't do anything, but... I want to at least be by your
side.

Melissa-chan seems to like coffee. She's reliable and gives
off an adult vibe.

It's a familiar fountain pen... Maybe it's a memento from my
grandmother.

These are the flowers that Ronoa-chan picked. They are
arranged so beautifully... She might have a talent for this
kind of thing.

This is Ryan's training sword. You can feel the dedication
from the wear and tear...

Rebecca's whip. The well-worn leather fits snugly in the
owner's hand, while the tip of the fall inflicts a pain that
clings to the victim's body.

It's just an ordinary clock. Time cannot be turned back, but
children are moving forward. ...I can't afford to lose
either.

The books on swordsmanship and military strategy are lined
up tightly. Ryan's earnestness is well portrayed...
...Oh? There's a hidden door behind the large books...?
Hey, sis!! You can't look there...!
